ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W3_CafeOrderApp

Class Name: CafeOrderApp

Difficulty: Level 2 — Multi-Class Application

Estimated Time: 45–60 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 38 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a console-based cafe order program using Scanner.
The user selects menu items by number and enters quantities.
The program stores the order and prints a final summary.

Program Flow
1. Create a Scanner.
2. Create several MenuItem objects.
3. Display the menu.
4. Repeatedly ask the user for a menu number.
5. If the user enters 0, finish the order.
6. Otherwise, ask for quantity.
7. Add the selected menu item to the Order.
8. Print the final order summary.

Class Responsibilities
CafeOrderApp controls input and program flow.
MenuItem stores menu data.
Order stores and calculates order data.